post_text:
Now through December 31, 2020, the USDA will allow BCSD schools to serve meals to any child ages 2-18. Children do not have to be enrolled in a BCSD school to receive a free breakfast and lunch. Grab and Go meals are available at every BCSD school site, with the exception of Rafer Johnson.

Students are also no longer required to be present to pick up meals. Parents and guardians can complete a “meal passport” for each of their children to pick up meals without their children. A completed meal passport must be provided at the time of pick up. Meal passports will be available for BCSD and non-BCSD students at school sites.

post_text: ‪Congratulations Nicole Negron, a teacher at Sierra Middle School, for being named a 2019-2020 Kern County Teacher of Year! #TeamBCSD ‬
shared_text:
KCSOS
May 8 at 5:02 PM ·

3rd grade teacher Wajeha Chaudhry from Loudon Elementary School and 7th grade English teacher Nicole Negron from Sierra Middle School have been named the 2019-20 Kern County Teachers of the Year. The finalists are now eligible to apply to move on to the California State Teachers of the Year program later in the year. An alternate, Joseph Andreotti, an 8th grade History/Social Science at Lakeside School, was also selected in the event that one of the finalists is unable to apply for the state competition. CONGRATS!

post_text: Cato Middle School students had a blast learning about the past. Students enjoyed a field trip to Hearst Castle. William Randolph Hearst, a tycoon in the news industry, began to build the elaborate estate in 1919. It would be many years before it was completed. Hearst Castle is now considered a National Historic Landmark. A great piece of history for our students to see! #TeamBCSD

post_text:
We are excited to announce that two of our BCSD music teachers have been selected to receive Kern County Music Educators Association (KCMEA) Awards.
Congratulations to Ms. Maritza Borja, KCMEA Choral Educator Award winner, and Mr. Marc Rodriguez, KCMEA Multicultural Music Educator Award winner!
Both Ms. Borja and Mr. Rodriguez will be recognized by KCMEA at the District’s Honor Concert ‪on Monday, April 20, 2020‬, at the Mechanics Band Theater. #TeamBCSD

post_text:
The Bakersfield City School District has been made aware of possible PG&E Public Safety Power Shut-offs (“PSPS”) that may affect some schools in our district.The safety of our students is always our top priority.

The District is closely monitoring PSPS events across the state. Should we receive information from PG&E confirming their intent to shut off power in areas that affect our schools, parents will be notified of any action taken by the district via Robocall, District and School websites, and the District’s social media pages. The District will continue monitoring the situation and notify our families and staff of any updates regarding this matter.

Thank you for your understanding and patience.

post_text: Congratulations to Katherine Scheler, Emerson Middle School teacher. She is the first recipient of the year to receive the One Classroom at a Time grant from KBAK-29 and Mor Furniture For Less. Her classroom will receive one thousand dollars for her project A Novel Approach. The money will be used to purchase classroom books for the students to enhance bilingual education. #TeamBCSD

CSUB.EDU
CSUB alumni teachers: Let’s hang a pennant in your classroom! | California State University, Bakersfield

CSUB Alumni Association
September 11, 2019 at 11:23 AM ·

ATTENTION ALUMNI TEACHERS!
What better way to put college – and your alma mater -- front and center in children’s minds than pinning a CSUB Alumni pennant up in your classroom?
So we are launching an effort to get as many CSUB Alumni pennants in as many classrooms of CSUB alumni teachers as possible. This story tells you more, and how you can get your pennant from us.

post_text: Get ready for back to school at one of BCSD's four Wellness Centers. #TeamBCSD members are ready to provide medical services, such as immunizations and physicals, to district students who are still in need of these services in time for school. Plus, the centers are open all year long to help support the overall health of our students. Call your child's school or one of our four centers today. Make sure your child is ready for the first day of school on August 14th!
